The Arc at Draycott for Rent
The Arc is a freehold condominium that is located in Draycott, Orchard. There are 58 units available at this condominium with built-up from 1,130 sf to 1,270 sf. It was developed by CapitaLand Ltd, and was completed in around 2010.
ENCLAVE OF PRIVILEGE THE ARC AT DRAYCOTT 5 DRAYCOTT DRIVE Located within the exclusive Ardmore Park-Draycott locale, this freehold development is BS Capital’s signature project and the measure.of private living at the highest levels of modernity and exclusivity. Designed byADDP Architects, The Arc at Draycot with its curved facade is one of the tallest buildings in this ultra prestigious vicinity. This delightful36-storeyabode in the sky conceals an engaging interior you will relish coming home lo. For starters, each level boasts no more than two residences, thereby heightening a sense of privacy that’s second to none. Inside each unit, glass curtain walls skin ultra-high ceilings, accentuating a fooling of expanse and space. Premium fittings from Philippe Storck, Miele, Gessi, and Ulti. The Arc’s sexy bathrooms are ensconced in premium marble and exquisite fillings and bordered by large windows framing the panoramic view of the city. It is all the better to enjoy a relaxing soak in your tub as you soak in the magnificent sights and surroundings. More than an abode in the city, The Arc Draycott is also an AEM haven for the active, thanks to the 50 metres lap pool, gym, and jacuzzi. Yes, the icing on the cake after each grueling workout is surely the knowledge that Orchard Road’s finest dining and shopping delights are a stone’s throw away.
Comparison with Nearby Condos
The Arc At Draycott stands out in the competitive landscape of luxury condominiums in Singapore, particularly when juxtaposed against neighboring developments such as 7 Draycott Drive, 38 Draycott Drive, and J C Draycott. Its modern architectural design and comprehensive suite of superior facilities, including a state-of-the-art gymnasium and a serene lap pool, set a high benchmark for upscale living in District 10. This emphasis on contemporary aesthetics and an array of lifestyle amenities is a testament to the development’s appeal to those seeking a blend of luxury and convenience.
Moreover, while the vicinity is home to other prestigious projects like Sky Vue, One Pearl Bank, and The Metropolitan Condominium, The Arc At Draycott distinguishes itself with its prime location nestled in the heart of Singapore’s most coveted residential area. Its proximity to the Orchard Road shopping belt and easy access to public transportation, such as the Orchard MRT station, enhances the living experience for residents. These factors, combined with the development’s luxurious offerings, make The Arc At Draycott a top choice for discerning tenants who prioritize a sophisticated and convenient lifestyle in Singapore.

Scotts Highpark is a freehold condominium development located at 45 Scotts Road Singapore 228232 in prestigious district 09. It is completed in 2009 by the reputable CapitaLand Residential. Living in the centre of Singapore’s number one Orchard Shopping district is a dream home for everyone. Two residential towers soar to a height of 19 and 27 storeys with sky gardens built at every four floors. The penthouse units here consist of single and duplex units which have private verandas and Jacuzzi. This enchanting tropical oasis has a total of 73 exquisite units comprising of 2-3 bedrooms (1141-2110 sqft) and penthouses (3466-4112 sqft).
Scotts High Park – Accessibilities
Scotts High Park is a prestigious freehold condominium located at 45 Scotts Road Singapore 228232, just off Orchard Road, in District 9 near Newton MRT Station. Orchard boulevard MRT Station and NS21 Newton MRT Station are the nearest to the condominium. Public transportation has made the lives of residents easy who do not have their own vehicles. Bus stops are also located at walking distances. This project is created with immense planning to provide all the basic needs to the residents. Easily accessible via the Pan Island Expressway (PIE), and the Central Expressway (CTE), Scotts Highpark definitely puts you at a vantage point. Newton, Orchard, and Novena MRT Station are located within walking distance. Other public transport is also readily available.
The Scotts High Park–Amenities and Attractions
There are different amenities located near this building. Numerous restaurants and eating establishments are in the vicinity and residents can go to the nearby Shopping Centre or the Market and Food Centre to fulfil more than just daily necessities. One of the many attractive aspects of Scotts Highpark is its close proximity to the vibrant Orchard Road shopping paradise and the popular Newton Circus Food Centre. Other malls in the vicinity include Far East Plaza, United Square, Novena Square, and Balmoral Plaza, where one can indulge in amenities such as food and shopping.

The architectural brilliance of the residences at Berth@the Cove complements the beauty of the surroundings, offering elegant and modern living spaces designed for comfort and opulence.
Residents here enjoy a range of world-class amenities, including private marina berths for yacht owners, a luxurious clubhouse, infinity pools, and well-equipped fitness centers.
The neighborhood provides a safe and secure environment, with 24/7 concierge services and top-notch security. Conveniently located, Berth@the Cove offers easy access to Sentosa’s vibrant entertainment and dining options, making it a paradise for those who seek a harmonious blend of luxury,
relaxation, and convenience. Experience the epitome of refined living at Berth@the Cove in Sentosa.

title: Pinetree Hill Condominium
description:
Near MRT stations:Dover MRT
District:D21 - Clementi Park/ Upper Bukit Timah

Pinetree Hill is a new launch condominium located in District 21’s Ulu Pandan vicinity. This exclusive development offers a serene living experience with its 520 units spread across three 24-storey residential towers. Situated on a 99-year leasehold site spanning 22,534.7 square meters, Pinetree Hill provides residents with unblocked views of Clementi Forest and Bukit Timah Nature Reserve.
Developed by United Venture Development, a joint venture between UOL Group and Singapore Land Group, Pinetree Hill stands out with its prime location and quality design. The development’s unit mix includes 1-bedroom + Study to 5-bedroom units, catering to diverse homebuyer preferences.
Residents can enjoy a wide range of facilities at Pinetree Hill, including a 50m lap pool, aquatherapy pool, tennis court, and a fully equipped gym. The PineTree Nest, offering captivating views of the surrounding greenery, adds a touch of resort-like ambience to the development.
Connectivity is convenient, with bus stops and services nearby, as well as Dover MRT station within a 15-minute walk. The upcoming Maju MRT station on the Cross-Island Line Phase 2 will further enhance accessibility for residents.
Families with school-going children will appreciate the proximity to renowned schools such as Henry Park Primary School and Pei Tong Primary School. Other reputable educational institutions in the area include Nan Hua Primary School, Methodist Girls’ School (Primary), and Singapore Polytechnic.
As part of the URA Masterplan, the Ulu Pandan neighborhood is set to undergo exciting developments. A proposed nature park, linear park, and green corridor along the Ulu Pandan Canal will provide residents with enhanced recreational spaces and connectivity. Additionally, a new commercial node near Dover MRT station will offer a variety of amenities and dining options.
Pinetree Hill presents an exceptional opportunity to experience nature-inspired living in a well-connected and vibrant neighborhood. With its prime location, thoughtfully designed units, and abundant facilities, this condominium is an ideal choice for those seeking a harmonious blend of tranquility and convenience.

Lentor Hills Residences: New Launch Condominium in Lentor Hills Road
Welcome to Lentor Hills Residences, a highly anticipated new condominium development located in Lentor Hills Road. With its strategic location and a wide range of residential units, this project offers a vibrant and modern living experience for residents.
Spanning a generous site area of 184,460 square feet, Lentor Hills Residences boasts 598 thoughtfully designed apartments. From cozy 1-bedroom units to spacious 4-bedroom layouts, there is a home to suit every lifestyle and preference.
One of the key highlights of Lentor Hills Residences is its exceptional connectivity. Situated just opposite the upcoming Lentor MRT station on the Thomson-East Coast line (TEL), residents will enjoy seamless access to the city and beyond. The TEL provides convenient connections to major transportation hubs, including Orchard Road, the Central Business District, and other parts of Singapore.
Within the development, residents will discover a host of impressive facilities and amenities. From a 50-meter lap pool for invigorating swims to a sky terrace with a garden bridge and a 400-meter jogging track for fitness enthusiasts, there are plenty of options to relax and stay active. Other notable features include a heated onsen for ultimate relaxation, play zone and work zone clubhouses, an Early Childhood Development Centre (ECDC), and work-from-anywhere (WFA) zones for flexibility and convenience.
Lentor Hills Residences is not just a place to call home; it is also part of a vibrant neighborhood that offers an abundance of amenities. Nearby shopping malls, such as Jubilee Square, Djitsun Mall, and AMK Hub, provide a diverse range of retail and dining options. For nature lovers, Thomson Nature Park and Lower Peirce Reservoir offer peaceful retreats to explore and enjoy outdoor activities.
Families with children will appreciate the proximity to reputable schools like Anderson Primary School, CHIJ St. Nicholas Girls’ Primary School, and Ang Mo Kio Primary School, ensuring a quality education for their little ones.
As part of the URA Masterplan, the Lentor neighborhood is set to undergo exciting developments, including the Punggol Digital District and the Cross Island Line (CRL). The CRL will enhance public transport connectivity, making it easier for residents to travel across the island.
With its prime location, well-designed units, and an array of amenities, Lentor Hills Residences presents an excellent opportunity for homebuyers and investors alike. Experience the best of contemporary living in this upcoming condominium and embrace a lifestyle of convenience, connectivity, and comfort.

Grand Dunman Condominium: Luxurious Living in District 15, Singapore
Experience the epitome of luxurious living at Grand Dunman Condominium. Situated in the highly sought-after District 15 along Dunman Road, this 99-year leasehold development offers an exceptional residential experience. With its stunning collection of 1 to 5-bedroom units, including dual key layouts, Grand Dunman Condominium promises unparalleled sophistication and breathtaking views.
Luxurious Living Spaces and Unobstructed Views
Grand Dunman Condominium features seven residential blocks, standing tall at 17 or 18 storeys, comprising a total of 1,008 meticulously designed units. Each unit is thoughtfully crafted to provide a harmonious blend of elegance, comfort, and functionality. Enjoy panoramic views of the city skyline or the serene sea from the outward-facing units, enhancing your daily living experience.
Unmatched Lifestyle Facilities and Amenities
Indulge in a wealth of lifestyle facilities at Grand Dunman Condominium. Dive into the spectacular 80-meter Grand Pool, unwind in the invigorating Hydro massage pool, or explore the enchanting treetop walk and playground. The development boasts two 3-storey clubhouses, the Jewel Clubhouse and Pool Clubhouse, offering a wide range of amenities such as shops, function rooms, a library, a viewing deck, games room, karaoke room, sauna, gym, and function rooms. Enjoy a world of luxury and entertainment right at your doorstep.
Strategic Location and Seamless Connectivity
Grand Dunman Condominium enjoys excellent connectivity to various transportation options. With Dakota MRT station just a two-minute walk away, residents have easy access to the Circle Line, connecting them to key destinations including the Central Business District (CBD), Paya Lebar, and the serene Botanic Gardens. The development is also well-served by numerous bus services, providing convenient commuting options. For those who prefer to drive, the Pan Island Expressway (PIE) and East Coast Parkway (ECP) offer seamless connectivity to Tampines, Changi, Jurong East, the CBD, and Changi Airport.
Surrounded by Vibrant Retail and Dining Destinations

title: Parc Life Executive Condominium
description:
Near MRT stations:Sembawang MRT,Canberra MRT
District:D27 - Sembawang/ Yishun

Parc Life Executive Condominium is a leasehold (99 yrs from 2014) development completed in 2018 and developed by SEMBAWANG RESIDENCES PTE LTD. The development occupies a land area of 22,404 sqm and a Gross Floor Area of 62,732 sqm. It has a total of 11 blocks and consists of 628 units. Located along Sembawang Crescent in Sembawang, in District 27, It is within walking distance to MRT stations such as Sembawang MRT, and Canberra MRT which provide residents easy access to other areas of Singapore.
Parc Life has met its Minimum Occupation Period (MOP) of 5 years in the year 2023.
The nearest schools are SEMBAWANG PRIMARY SCHOOL and SEMBAWANG SECONDARY SCHOOL. Other nearby amenities include: 3 Childcare Centre(s): PPIS CHILD DEVELOPMENT CENTRE – SEMBAWANG VISTA, PCF SPARKLETOTS PRESCHOOL @ CANBERRA Blk 330 (DS), MY FIRST SKOOL, and 3 Grocerie(s): NTUC FAIRPRICE CO-OPERATIVE LTD, COLD STORAGE SINGAPORE (1983) PTE LTD, NTUC FAIRPRICE CO-OPERATIVE LTD, and 3 Kindergarten(s): PCF SPARKLETOTS PRESCHOOL @ GAMBAS Blk 317 (KN), PCF SPARKLETOTS PRESCHOOL @ CANBERRA Blk 330 (DS), PCF SPARKLETOTS PRESCHOOL @ GAMBAS Blk 309 (KN), and 2 Shopping Mall(s): SUN PLAZA, SEMBAWANG SHOPPING CENTRE.
Buyers and tenants are attracted to District 27, which encompasses Sembawang and Yishun. Sembawang is named after the Sembawang tree in Sembawang Park, a 15ha tranquil park with a natural beach. Originally the site of the Nee Soon Rubber estate, Sembawang has evolved into a suburban estate with three shopping malls and two MRT stations. It also hosts Sembawang Camp, a major navel base for the Singapore Army. Part of Sembawang is also an industrial area. The town houses a commercial dockyard, known as Sembawang Shipyard, which offers modern marine repair services. Yishun is home to Northpoint City, a sizeable shopping mall with a public library. Other notable places include the Yishun Integrated Transport Hub, which has an air-conditioned bus interchange with a link to Yishun MRT station, Khoo Teck Puat Hospital, which offers a comprehensive range of medical services and specialist care, and Chong Pang, which houses a wet market and various hawker centres. Covering 13,500ha, the North Region is one of the five regions in Singapore. Located further from the Central Business District (CBD), the North Region offers ample greenery as well as a variety of work and play options. These include integrated developments such as Bukit Canberra, an integrated sport and community hub, and the upcoming Woodlands Health Campus, which will open progressively from the end of 2023. When fully opened, the Woodlands Health Campus will have around 1,400 beds to cater to residents in the North Region. The region will also benefit from enhanced connectivity as strategized in the Master Plan 2019. More cycling paths and park connectors will be constructed, with the WoodsVista Gallery offering pedestrian and cycling pathways connecting Woodlands MRT, Admiralty Park and Woodlands Waterfront Park. More details on WoodsVista Gallery and the transformation atWoodlands Regional Centre Master plan

Step-by-Step Guide on Successfully Purchasing HDB Resales
1. Determine your eligibility by having yourHFE letterReady: Check if you meet the eligibility criteria set by the Housing and Development Board (HDB). Ensure you are a Singapore Citizen (SC), at least 21 years old, and fulfill other requirements.
2. Set a budget: Assess your financial situation and determine the budget for yourHDB resalepurchase. Consider factors such as loan eligibility, down payment, and monthly mortgage payments.
3. Engage aproperty agent: Seek the assistance ofBUYCONDO Teamwho have extensive knowledge of theHDB resale market. They can help you find suitable options, negotiate prices, and guide you through the entire process.
4. Search for available HDB resale flats: Utilize online platforms like the HDB resale portal or engage with agents to search for available flats near Jurong Point. Narrow down your options based on location, size, and pricing.
5. Arrange for viewings: Schedule viewings of the shortlisted flats to assess their suitability. Pay attention to factors such as proximity to amenities, transportation, and the overall condition of the flat.
6. Conveyancing matters: Engage a solicitor to handle the legal aspects of the transaction, including conducting title searches, preparing the Option to Purchase (OTP), and facilitating the completion of the resale process.
7. Negotiate and submit the offer: Work with your property agent to negotiate the price and submit the offer to the seller. Keep in mind the valuation price and market trends to make informed decisions.
8. Exercise the Option to Purchase (OTP): Once the offer is accepted, exercise the OTP by paying a deposit (up to $5,000 of the purchase price). This gives you a 21-day exclusive period to proceed with the resale process.
9. Secure financing: Apply for an HDB loan or bank loan to secure the financing for yourHDB resale purchase. Compare loan packages, interest rates, and repayment terms to choose the most suitable option.
10. Arrange for a second appointment: After securing financing, arrange for a second appointment with HDB to complete the resale process. During this appointment, both buyer and seller will sign the necessary documents.
11. Pay the remaining amount: Prior to the completion appointment, make the necessary payments, including the down payment, stamp duty, and legal fees.
12. Completion appointment: Attend the completion appointment at the HDB office, where the remaining funds will be disbursed, and ownership of the flat will be transferred.
13. Renovation and moving in: After completing the resale transaction, make arrangements for renovation works and plan your move-in date. Ensure compliance with HDBrenovation guidelines.

CPF Monthly Salary Ceiling Cap
Each month, we have to contribute up to 20% of our salary, and our employers have to contribute up to 17% of our salary to our CPF accounts up to a salary cap of $6,000. This percentage may vary depending on our age and our income. As announced in Budget 2023, this salary cap is set to increase to $8,000 by 2026.
Besides the coming rise in the CPF Monthly Salary Ceiling, both Employee’s CPF contributions and Employer’s CPF contributions for seniors aged 55 to 70 will also increase in the coming years. If we fall into this age range, our overall compensation will go up, but we may see a slightly lower take-home pay as we are also makinghigher CPF contributions.

LTD., MY FIRST SKOOL, and 3 Grocerie(s): NTUC FAIRPRICE CO-OPERATIVE LTD, COLD STORAGE SINGAPORE (1983) PTE LTD, NTUC FAIRPRICE CO-OPERATIVE LTD, and 3 Kindergarten(s): PCF SPARKLETOTS PRESCHOOL @ BUKIT TIMAH Blk 319 (KN), PCF SPARKLETOTS PRESCHOOL @ CLEMENTI Blk 330 (KN), Early Years Montessori, and 3 Shopping Mall(s): THE CLEMENTI MALL, NEWest (U/C – TOP : 31 Dec 2018), HONG LEONG GARDEN SHOPPING CENTRE.
Buyers and tenants are attracted to District 5, which spans across the Buona Vista, Clementi, Dover, Pasir Panjang and West Coast neighbourhoods. It is a popular choice for home buyers due to its relative proximity to the Core Central Region. With a variety of amenities such as restaurants, bars and shops, parks, gyms and business properties in the area, District 5 is perfect for residents looking for a lively location with both work and play spaces. District 5 has a good mix of properties in terms of affordability, ranging from HDB flats to luxury condominiums to landed properties. District 5 also has several commercial and industrial properties around Clementi MRT, at Star Vista and One North. The district is also well connected by MRT stations such as Clementi, Dover, Buona Vista, One-North, Kent Ridge, Haw Par Villa, and Pasir Panjang Mrt Stations along the East-West and Circle lines. District 5 Is also particularly car-friendly. Residents with cars are well served by the Ayer Rajah Expressway and the West Coast Highway.
With a land area of 25,500ha, the West Region is the largest of the five regions in Singapore. Jurong East is the regional centre of the region, while Jurong West is the most populous town in the region. Many of Singapore’s heavy industry companies are concentrated in the West Region. These are mainly petrochemical companies comprising international players such as BP, ExxonMobil, DuPont, Mitsui Chemicals and Shell. The West Region is also at the forefront of the government’s industrial development efforts. The government plans to develop the Jurong Lake District and Jurong Innovation District into Singapore’s second Central Business District (CBD) area. Additionally, upon completion in the 2040s, the Tuas Mega Port is anticipated to be the world’s single-largest container port with an annual capacity of 65 million TEUs.

Executive Condominiums(ECs) and Condominiums (Condos) are both popular housing options in Singapore, but they have distinct differences that set them apart.
Eligibility: ECs target Singaporeans who do not meet the income and asset criteria for purchasing private properties. The eligibility criteria for ECs are set by the government and are subject to change. On the other hand, there are no restrictions on who can purchase a condo, and foreign nationals are also eligible to buy a condo in Singapore.Price: ECs are generally priced lower than condos due to their eligibility criteria and government restrictions. This makes ECs more affordable for many Singaporeans looking to own a home.Amenities: ECs have amenities similar to those found in private condos, including swimming pools, gymnasiums, and clubhouse facilities. However, the amenities in ECs are typically smaller and not as extensive as those in private condos.Resale Restrictions: ECs have resale restrictions for the first five years after the government issuance of the Temporary Occupation Permit (TOP). During this time, EC unit owners are only allowed to sell their units to Singaporeans or Permanent Residents (PRs).After the five-year minimum occupancy period (MOP), EC unit owners may sell their units to all eligible buyers, including foreign nationals, subject to conditions set by the government. There are no such restrictions on the resale of condos.Maintenance Fees: ECs must set aside a certain amount of funds for their maintenance and upgrading this is the same as condo owners.Location: ECs are usually located in the suburbs, away from the central business district, whereas condos are more likely to be found in central areas, near the city centre.Design and Layout: ECs are usually built with standard designs and layouts, whereas condos offer more customization options, including different unit types and layouts.
In conclusion, ECs and condos offer different advantages and disadvantages. While ECs (New Launch or 5 MOP Turn Privatised) are more affordable and cater to the housing needs of Singaporeans, condos offer more freedom, amenities, and customization options.
Ultimately, choosing between an EC and a condo will depend on individual circumstances, such as income, family size, and personal preferences.
